This paper deals with statistical learning theory and model selection, which are topics commonly studied in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses information criteria and their asymptotic behavior, which falls under the subfield of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper mentions the Bayes generalization loss and the use of hyperparameters, which are relevant to the subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and statistics (cs.ST). Finally, the paper discusses the algebraic geometrical structure of learning machines, which is a topic studied in the subfield of systems and control (cs.SY).
